Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in your `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity => { /* app losing focus */ })
        .OnStop(activity => { /* app fully backgrounded */ }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* app backgrounded */ }));
#endif
});
```

**Key points:**

- **Android `OnPause`** = lost focus (maps to the cross-platform `Deactivated` event). **`OnStop`** = fully backgrounded (maps to `Stopped`).
- **iOS `DidEnterBackground`** = fully backgrounded (also maps to `Stopped`).
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.

**Cross-platform alternative:** If you don't need the native callback parameters, you can simply override `OnStopped()` on a `Window` subclass — it fires on both platforms when the app backgrounds:

```csharp
protected override void OnStopped()
{
    base.OnStopped();
    // Runs on Android OnStop and iOS DidEnterBackground
}
```
